<strong>THE STORY:</strong> In the not-too-distant future, the pressure to cure a global pandemic spurs the creation of DEINDE, a device that allows a team of brilliant quantum biologists to think directly into a powerful computer. At first, they use this prosthetic for the mind under strict rules of engagement, but soon noble ideals and personal passions lead a few to break the rules. They discover that DEINDE’s power is far greater than anyone first imagined, and their world spins out of control, raising questions of morality, consciousness, and what it means to be human in an age of rapid technological change.

DEINDE is presented as part of <a href="http://www.bfgcollective.com/" target="_blank">The BFG Collective</a> at The Secret Theatre with <a href="http://www.boomerangtheatre.org/boom/index2.php" target="_blank">Boomerang Theatre Company</a> and <a href="http://www.gideonth.com/" target="_blank">Gideon Productions</a>.
